body:
Hi! 👋 

Firstly, thanks for your work on this project! 🙂

Today I used [patch-package](https://github.com/ds300/patch-package) to patch `exceljs@4.4.0` for the project I'm working on.

ExcelJS fails at generating excels that have a lot of data. This is because of inefficient data structures the present out of memory issues during the stream of data to XML. One big inefficiency is the pushing of XML tags and data one by one which causes the out of range issue. By converting the open tag + data + close tag into one element array instead of 3, we can make the data structure a lot more space efficient. 

Here is the diff that solved my problem:

```diff
diff --git a/node_modules/exceljs/lib/utils/xml-stream.js b/node_modules/exceljs/lib/utils/xml-stream.js
index 46a5969..776d5de 100644
--- a/node_modules/exceljs/lib/utils/xml-stream.js
+++ b/node_modules/exceljs/lib/utils/xml-stream.js
@@ -57,8 +57,7 @@ class XmlStream {
     this._stack.push(name);

     // start streaming node
-    xml.push(OPEN_ANGLE);
-    xml.push(name);
+    xml.push(`${OPEN_ANGLE}${name}`);
     pushAttributes(xml, attributes);
     this.leaf = true;
     this.open = true;
@@ -105,9 +104,7 @@ class XmlStream {
     if (this.leaf) {
       xml.push(CLOSE_SLASH_ANGLE);
     } else {
-      xml.push(OPEN_ANGLE_SLASH);
-      xml.push(node);
-      xml.push(CLOSE_ANGLE);
+      xml.push(`${OPEN_ANGLE_SLASH}${node}${CLOSE_ANGLE}`);
     }
     this.open = false;
     this.leaf = false;
```

<em>This issue body was [partially generated by patch-package](https://github.com/ds300/patch-package/issues/296).</em>
